<HEADLINE>
PATRIOTS' SIMMONS RECEIVING KUDOS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JOE BURRIS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Patriots wide receiver/kick returner Troy
Brown suffered a left ankle sprain on the first play of Sunday's
game against the Kansas City Chiefs. At the time, Tony Simmons had
no idea how much his afternoon had been altered.
</P>
<P>
   Brown is the team's best reserve receiver, and when he failed to
return, Simmons was summoned to take his place. Not only did the
second-year player from Wisconsin fill in, but he had arguably the
best game of his career.
</P>
<P>
   Simmons led everyone with seven catches for 107 yards, an
average of 15.3 yards, in New England's 16-14 loss. He entered the
game with seven catches for 103 yards. His catch total was a career
high and his yardage was second only to the 109 he had against
Indianapolis Nov. 1.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tony played very well for us,'' said Patriots quarterback Dedsoe. ``He had a number of plays were he was my side adjustment.
They were blitzing, and he came in and did a good job with that and
got some run after the catch.
</P>
<P>
   ``He made a great play for us late in the game. He's generally
our fourth receiver, but as I continue to say, even our fourth guy
can play really well.''
</P>
<P>
   Actually he's the fifth-best statistically, but Sunday he was
tops. Bledsoe was referring to a 39-yard completion to Simmons in
the forth quarter on first and 10 from Kansas City's 49. The
Patriots scored their second touchdown two plays later.
</P>
<P>
   ``I went inside the corner, ran up the field, Drew saw me at the
last minute and just threw it up there,'' said Simmons. ``I just
had to make sure I stayed away from the safety.''
</P>
<P>
   Before that play, Simmons caught an 8-yard slant, a play during
which he snatched the ball out of the hands of Kansas City
cornerback Cris Dishman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was just getting open, helping Drew out there if I could,''
said Simmons. ``When Troy went out, I kind of figured maybe I would
be up for a while until . . . his situation was undisclosed, so I
didn't know.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just played the best that I could, and when I got open, I
just hoped Drew saw me. They were doing a lot of blitzing, but I
just had to go up and get the ball.''
</P>
<P>
   Despite his shining play, Simmons regretted the loss.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just can't pass up a situation like that,'' he said. ``We
can't give up the ball, we have to have no turnovers, especially a
team like that. Any team. And we're in their house, too. We turn
the ball over and that kills you in this type of game.''
</P>
<P>
   There is no telling if Simmons will get more work now. But the
player he replaced was impressed with his effort.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tony stepped in and played great,'' said Brown. ``He made some
big plays down the stretch.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
