<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-SANTAANITA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT'S A WILD DAY FOR BAFFERT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA _ You can't win 'em all. It turns out not even Bob
Baffert can win 'em all.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert's Breeders' Cup preparations suffered setbacks at
odds-on Sunday when leading California 2-year-old Forest Camp lost
to Dixie Union in a fast-paced Norfolk Stakes at sunny Santa Anita
and 3-year-old superfilly Silverbulletday was simply outrun by
Beautiful Pleasure in the Beldame at soggy Belmont Park.
</P>
<P>
   But in between, it was another huge day for the nation's
dominant thoroughbred barn as River Keen and jockey Chris Antley
scored a 12-1 upset over Behrens in the $1million Jockey Club Gold
Cup at Belmont and 2-year-old Captain Steve and Garrett Gomez led
gate to wire in the Lane's End Breeders' Futurity at Keeneland.
</P>
<P>
   So it was easy for Baffert to look at the bright side after
Forest Camp was beaten half a length by a more relaxed Dixie Union
and Alex Solis, who rallied from fourth on the outside at 4-1,
reversing their Del Mar Futurity finish.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't go that fast (early),'' Baffert said after Forest
Camp set a :221/5-:454/5 pace. ``Now I don't have to be the
favorite (in the Breeders' Cup Juvenile).''
</P>
<P>
   Both horses ran big races, Forest Camp losing for the first time
in three starts, Dixie Union winning his fourth in five starts and
running a quick mile (1:35.79).
</P>
<P>
   ``He's never run a bad race,'' trainer Richard Mandella said.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert, likely to have the strongest contingent in Breeders'
Cup history Nov. 6 at Florida's Gulfstream Park, had assured
himself of the favorite's role in the Juvenile Fillies when
Chilukki stayed undefeated Saturday in the Oak Leaf Stakes. But
that was just a warmup for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert Coast to Coast began shortly after noon Santa Anita time
when Silverbulletday and Jerry Bailey chased loose leader Beautiful
Pleasure and Jorge Chavez throughout the Beldame. It was 3-year-old
Silverbulletday's first race against older females.
</P>
<P>
   Half an hour later, in the 1\-mile Gold Cup, the major prep for
the Breeders' Cup Classic, River Keen took a perfect stalking trip
to a 3\-length victory. Baffert had hinted Saturday that a hoof
crack would force the 7-year-old to be scratched.
</P>
<P>
   River Keen will run in the Classic with barnmate General
Challenge, who assumes the top ranking among active 3-year-olds
after Belmont Stakes winner Lemon Drop Kid's fifth in the Gold Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Five-year-old Behrens, the nation's top-ranked racehorse,
struggled to edge Dubai's Almutawakel for second.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
