<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-11 02:11 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2943 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s BC-BBA-INDIANS-RAMIREZ-B     10-11 0618
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-INDIANS-RAMIREZ-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RED SOX HAVE RAMIREZ'S NUMBER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK BLAUDSCHUN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ The numbers suggested something better _ a club-record
165 runs batted in, 44 home runs, .333 batting average, 131 runs
scored.
</P>
<P>
   MVP numbers for sure.
</P>
<P>
   But that was another lifetime _ back during a regular season
that was all but meaningless for a Cleveland Indians team that had
the AL Central title locked up since the All-Star break.
</P>
<P>
   The numbers in the postseason indicate something else. No hits,
no runs batted in, and a queasy feeling that what looked so easy a
few days ago, when the Indians were up 2-0 on the Red Sox in the
American League Division Series has turned into a struggle for
survival.
</P>
<P>
   Will the real Manny Ramirez please take one step forward?
</P>
<P>
   Not the one that went 0 for 12 in the first two games against
the Red Sox and not the one that went 0 for 3 with a pair of walks
in Sunday night's wild 23-7 loss to the Red Sox at Fenway which
forced Sunday night's fifth and deciding game. But the cleanup
hitter in a lineup that during the regular season was as dangerous
top to bottom as any in baseball.
</P>
<P>
   Before Sunday &UR;  &LR; night's game, Mike Hargrove offered a logical
explanation. ``I don't think he's in a slump,'' said the Indians
manager. ``He's been pitched well. They (the Red Sox pitchers) are
hitting their spots.''
</P>
<P>
   Of course, the way the Red Sox hit against half a dozen Indian
pitchers, it didn't matter what Ramirez was or wasn't doing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everything we threw up there they hit,'' said Hargrove.
</P>
<P>
   The same could not be said of Ramirez, whose batting average is
a clean .000 through four games.
</P>
<P>
   Explanations are not easy to come by under such circumstances,
even tougher when Ramirez is involved.
</P>
<P>
   After all, this is the same player who was in a similar batting
funk after the first two games against the Red Sox in last year's
Division Series.
</P>
<P>
   His solution? When he arrived in Boston for Game 3, he dyed his
hair orange _ and responded with a pair of home runs in a 4-3
Cleveland victory as the Indians went on to win the series.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez never has embraced the spotlight, which is brighter in
postseason play.
</P>
<P>
   A couple of years ago, he simply had to do his job as the
Indians right fielder in the bottom third of Hargrove's lineup.
When Albert Belle ran off to Baltimore with free agent money,
Hargrove needed a new cleanup hitter.
</P>
<P>
   Why not Ramirez, who slowly had established himself since the
Indians chose him in the first round of the June 1991 draft?
</P>
<P>
   ``Why?'' asked Ramirez, who said he was comfortable batting
where he was batting.
</P>
<P>
   To say Ramirez hears tunes that the rest of us do not is
understating the issue.
</P>
<P>
   Just ask one of the Indians' clubhouse boys, the one whom
Ramirez asked to get his car washed. A natural question of how to
pay for this service was asked.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's money in the glove compartment,'' said Ramirez.
</P>
<P>
   Money? Indeed. Try $10,000.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez was once stopped and cited for three minor traffic
violations. After waiting while the police officer wrote the
ticket, Ramirez pulled out, made a U-turn and was pulled over
again.
</P>
<P>
   Pure Ramirez, whose basic philosophy about baseball, and perhaps
life, is, ``Sometimes they get me. And sometimes I get them.''
</P>
<P>
   Sunday &UR;  &LR; night in a game of vital importance for both the Red Sox
and the Indians, the Red Sox got the Indians and Ramirez, jumping
to a 15-2 lead in the first four innings before the Indians tried
unsuccessfully to climb back into contention.
</P>
<P>
   Fittingly, he ended his offensive effort in the ninth by taking
a called third strike.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-11-99 0211EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
