 &HT;    Magazine offers sneak peek at `Pokemon Yellow' game
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ One of the most anticipated new games of the coming
holiday season is ``Pokemon Yellow,'' the latest in the series of
Gameboy titles featuring this little Japanese character and
friends. There's a preview in the October issue of Nintendo Power
magazine. The reviewer says the game's maze world is all-new.
Samples of this new map are included as part of the article.
</P>
<P>
   Check out Apple's newest portable computer, the iBook, in the
October issue of MacWorld. The iBook is featured in the magazine's
cover story, which explains how the iBook differs from Apple's
other portable computers. The iBook also includes new wireless
technology that lets several users connect simultaneously to the
Internet through one device.
</P>
<P>
   ON CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   There's a new flight simulator on the market called ``Fly.''
Published by Gathering and developed by Terminal Reality, ``Fly''
offers a simulation in sound, sight and feel of flying a host of
airplanes. The game is available for both Macs and PCs.
</P>
<P>
   FileMaker has released its latest version of the database of the
same name. Called FileMaker Pro 5.0, this version includes features
that let users share databases over the intranet and develop more
powerful Web pages. FileMaker is available for both Macs and PCs.
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE
</P>
<P>
   One of the areas moving rapidly to the Web is employment
classified ads and job services. There are plenty of new sites
offering job openings and help in finding jobs. Now there's a site
that monitors all the other job sites. It's called Career-Builder
Mega Job Search. Career-Builder lets you monitor such popular sites
as Monster.com, CareerPath and Hotjobs. You'll find this site at
www.careerbuilder.com.
</P>
