</P>
<P>
   KIDS-LUNCHES _ ATLANTA _ Processed foods are convenient for
kids' lunches, and they love them, so what's the problem? Many of
them aren't nutritionally sound, and in fact, contain high amounts
of fats and sugars, and that may be contributing to a growing
epidemic of childhood obesity. That's one of the topics the
American Dietetic Association will be taking up when it opens its
annual meeting in Atlanta Oct. 17. We'll also talk to kids about
what their favorite processed meals/snacks are, and survey what
they're eating. (Walker/Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
