   BREAST-CANCER _ If you're a woman who has not been diagnosed
with breast cancer, it's probably one of your deepest fears. And if
you're a breast cancer survivor, you're looking for ways to enhance
lives and ensure a brighter future. For October, which is Breast
Health Awareness Month, we've assembled a list of positive things
anyone can do to make a difference. (Dayton Daily News).
</P>
