<HEADLINE>
BOOKS RECENTLY REVIEWED IN THE BOSTON GLOBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Nelson Mandela'' by Anthony Sampson (Knopf, $30). An
authorized biography of the former South African president. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Lovers for a Day: New and Collected Stories'' by Ivan Klima
(Grove, $24). Tales of the ironies and distractions of love, by the
prolific Czech writer. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``A Star Called Henry: Volume One of `The Last Roundup' '' by
Roddy Doyle (Viking, $24.95). A young Dubliner's coming of age amid
the violent history of modern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Last Life'' by Claire Messud (Harcourt Brace, $24). A
haunting novel of a family's flight from Algeria to France. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Places Left Unfinished at the Time of Creation'' by John
Phillip Santos (Viking, $24.95). A lyrical memoir of a life on both
sides of the Texas-Mexico border. &QL;
