<HEADLINE>
`THE RAGE' IS NO MATCH FOR THE ORIGINAL `CARRIE' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Rage: Carrie 2'' _ Too little, too late.
This marketer's dream is a lightweight compared with Brian
DePalma's nightmarish original. Released in 1976, ``Carrie''
features Sissy Spacek and Piper Laurie in a mother-daughter matchup
worthy of Joan and Christina Crawford. Rent that instead of this
sorry successor.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jacob the Liar'' _ Forget about Robin Williams in ``Jakob the
Liar.'' This 1977 German original, directed by Frank Beyer, is the
version to see. The remarkable story of a storyteller who keeps
alive the dreams of concentration-camp prisoners is told with
unsentimental skill.
</P>
<P>
   ``Shakespeare's Women &AMP; Claire Bloom'' _ The marvelous
exploration of a great playwright led by an exceptional actress
proves that educational and entertaining are not mutually
exclusive. Great family viewing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Gulliver's Travels'' _ Max Fleischer, Paramount's version of
Walt Disney, made the 1939 animated classic with great technical
skill and faithfulness to the Jonathan Swift tale. The newly
remastered version gives younger viewers a good idea what great
classic animation looks like, with its marvelous attention to
details.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: In just three weeks, ``The Matrix'' has generated
$23.4 million in sales, according to Daily Variety, smashing the
mark recently held by ``Titanic.'' It's the first time that a DVD
has outgrossed a VHS version, with 52 percent buying the DVD.
According to VideoScan, a company that tracks home video sales,
Warners sold 400,000 ``Matrix'' DVDs through traditional retail
outlets, and the figures aren't all in from on-line sales.Reel.com,
one of the leading Internet DVD providers, says that it's already
sold 50,000 ``Matrix'' DVDs.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Oct. 19: ``The Wizard of Oz'' (remastered
and DVD), ``eXistenZ,'' ``The Nuttiest Nutcracker,'' ``Color of
Courage,'' ``Children of the Corn 6,'' ``Metroland,'' ``Life,'' ``A
Walk on the Moon.'' Oct. 26: ``The Blair Witch Project,''
``Tactical Assault,'' ``The Velocity of Gary,'' ``Hideous Kinky,''
``Arlington Road.'' Nov. 9: ``Life Is Beautiful'' (dubbed
English-language version), ``Instinct,'' ``The Castle,''
``Heaven,'' ``Break Up,'' ``Rogue Trader.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-11-99 1514EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
