form Monday that would postpone a vote on a treaty banning nuclear
testing until President Clinton left office. Clinton put in writing
a request to delay action, and leading senators from both parties
circulated a letter that would satisfy a condition from the Senate
majority leader that the president himself said he would not meet:
to postpone the vote until the end of the Clinton presidency. By
