<P>
   HKN-THRASHERS _ They've only been in town for about a month, but
many of the Thrashers' players are already Braves fans. ``Most
hockey players are big baseball fans, at least the ones who grew up
in North America,'' said Ray Ferraro, who played in the Little
League World Series with Canadian champion Trail, British Columbia.
Hockey may be the dominant sport in Canada, but it isn't a
year-round sport for kids. ``We grew up playing baseball in the
summer,'' said Nelson Emerson. About a half dozen Thrashers players
went to a Braves playoff game against Houston and several hope to
go again Tuesday or Wednesday against the Mets. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16.
