<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   RAMSEY _ BOULDER, Colo. _ Barring any news developments, scene
piece from Boulder, Colo. as media and authorities revisit the
Ramsey case. (Schneider, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   ALA-LOTTERY _ BIRMINGHAM _ Alabama votes Tuesday on a statewide
lottery. (Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BIRM-MAYOR _ BIRMINGHAM _ A runoff is expected, but Birmingham
voters will take a big step Tuesday toward picking a successor to
20-year Mayor Richard Arrington. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   MILLION-MARCH _ Minister Ava Muhammad, Southern Regional
Representative for the Nation of Islam, will hold a press
conference Monday to announce plans for the Million Family March
scheduled for next year. The announcement comes four years after
the Nation organized the Million Man March on Washington. Muhammad,
the first woman in Islamic history to head a mosque, will also have
a special announcement regarding the Nation's leader, Minister
Louis Farrakhan, who is rumored to be in bad health. (Blake,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-FLOOD _ MEXICO CITY _ It's a frequent sight in Mexico.
Clusters of houses perched on steep hillsides, waiting for
disaster. After torrential rains last week, one such community was
buried in a killer mudslide that claimed scores of lives. It
happened in Acapulco in 1997, too. The causes of such tragedies _
often clearly avoidable _ stem from Mexico's poverty and this
country's lack of a culture of prevention. People often build
flimsy structures in areas vulnerable to disaster, and authorities
do nothing to warn of pending danger. (Ferriss, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6:30 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-HEAT _ TEL AVIV _ The Miami Heat plays NBA preseason game
vs Israeli champion Maccabi in Tel Aviv. We tag along to get
Israeli reaction, treatment of the players during their visit and
cover the game. (Kaplow, Cox News Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the (i) International and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   AFL-CIO _ LOS ANGELES _ Vice President Al Gore appears to have
the endorsement of the AFL-CIO labor federation locked up, but the
victory may be a hollow one if the unions decide to focus on
congressional races next year instead of the presdiency. Labor
leaders and House minority leader Dick Gephardt, D-Mo., discuss the
labor effort Monday at the AFL-CIO convention. (Shepard, Cox News
Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   ALANKEYES _ KANSAS CITY _ Alan Keyes was preaching to the
converted this weekend at a covention of conservatives in Kansas
City. It was a rare venture outside the television studio for the
best orator in the field who is conducting a largely electronic
(and free media) campaign. (Baxter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
