<SLUG> BC-DATABASE-AOL-UPGRADE-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
(ATTN: VA.) 
 AOL VERSION 5.0 OFFERS MANY NEW FEATURES
</HEADLINE>
   (mk) 
 By LONNIE BROWN   
 Lakeland (Fla.) Ledger   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   About a year ago, America Online released a major upgrade to the
program used to connect to the Virginia-based company's computers _
as well as to other users and to the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, AOL Version 5.0 was released. AOL users can download
by clicking on the Version 5.0 icon that occasionally pops up on
the welcome screen.
</P>
<P>
   There are a lot of new features that subscriberfind
useful. Overall, the new welcome screen is a bit more
commercialized than the Version 4.0 one. It's bigger, and that
provides more space for teasers to AOL partners and sponsors. One
of those is Kodak's ``You've Got Pictures,'' which allows
shutterbugs to drop off their pictures at a local processing
company and have them delivered to their Internet account, where
they can then be forwarded to friends as e-mail.
</P>
<P>
   Appealing to a broader customer base is the ability to have
screen names longer than 10 letters, and to have seven names under
one account as opposed to five. Keep in mind that only one screen
name can be online at one time.
</P>
<P>
   Another nice feature: Users can enter personal data into an
online calendar to remind them of appointments or recurring events.
If they like, they can indicate their interest in new CD or movie
releases and AOL can add ones selected to the calendar as well.
</P>
<P>
   The welcome screen that pops up initially each time AOL is
called is bigger and contains all the AOL channels _ the term AOL
gives to its various sections ranging from weather to health.
There's a section of the screen called ``My Places'' where users
can put up to five of their most-visited spots on AOL (portfolios,
hobbies, etc.) and then go to that spot with one click of the
mouse.
</P>
<P>
   Steve Case, AOL's chief executive officer, said he believes
users will like the ``all-new, much-improved AOL Search,'' now
offering a comprehensive list of results ranked by relevancy.
</P>
<P>
   ``The new AOL Search enables you to easily and efficiently
search the entire Internet and all of AOL's exclusive content in
one fell swoop,'' Case said. ``Drawing from more than 675,000
hand-selected listings, AOL Search will deliver a comprehensive,
ranked list of results, including both categories and specific
sites. This is the only search product on the Internet that
includes all of AOL's content and content from the Web.''
</P>
<P>
   Wish you had that e-mail back that you sent to the electronic
waste basket? AOL will now store deleted mail for up to 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Borrowing from the ability of other browsers, AOL now lets users
create personalized signatures that are automatically added to
e-mail messages. The signatures can include contact information, a
personal quote or other information.
</P>
<P>
   Users can now sign on AOL automatically and download e-mail and
newsgroups under multiple screen names without disconnecting and
reconnecting. The new version also makes it easy to save ``favorite
places'' and ``address book'' information for transfer to another
computer.
</P>
<P>
   And if you've ever wondered where the file that you downloaded
wound up, the download manager now has a ``locate'' button.
</P>
<P>
   AOL wants to be everywhere _ not just on computer monitors. Case
said the company is also introducing AOL e-Mail on Palm Pilots. The
software lets users read and respond to e-mail using the popular
organizers from 3Com. Later, AOL-Plus will be available for
high-speed network connections. When it detects high--speed access,
it will automatically load enhanced AOL features, including video,
audio and games.
</P>
<P>
   The bigger welcome screen and the additional features make the
program worth the time it takes to download and the small effort
needed to install it.
</P>
<P>
   (The Ledger in Lakeland, Fla., is part of the New York Times
Regional Newspaper Group.)
</P>
</TEXT>
