<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Keys for the Mets to win NLCS
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ 1. Mike Piazza's thumb.
</P>
<P>
   New York expects its All-Star catcher back after a throbbing
thumb knocked him out of the last two Division Series games. But
how effective will he be?
</P>
<P>
   _ 2. Kenny Rogers' pysche.
</P>
<P>
   A huge lift after being obtained at midseason from Oakland,
Rogers continues to struggle in the postseason, a habit he had as a
Yankee.
</P>
<P>
   _ 3. Run, Rickey, run.
</P>
<P>
   Ripped for indifferent play in the last two series with the
Braves, left fielder Rickey Henderson was hardly a 40-year-old
has-been in the LDS (.400, six stolen bases). The Mets need more of
the same.
</P>
<P>
   _ 4. Turner Field stigma.
</P>
<P>
   Since the Braves moved into The Ted, they have beaten the Mets
14 times in 18 tries in their new home. New York needs to break
out.
</P>
<P>
   _ 5. 100 Club.
</P>
<P>
   For the first time, the Mets had three players reach 100 RBIs in
the same season _ Piazza, Edgardo Alfonzo and Robin Ventura.
Against Arizona, they drove in seven of the club's 22 runs, but
Alfonzo got all but one of them. The middle of the order needs more
consistency against the Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas Stinson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
