</P>
<P>
   MOGUL-ARREST (Rome) _ Giancarlo Parretti, a flamboyant former
Hollywood mogul with longstanding international arrest warrants
hanging over him for convictions on perjury and other frauds, was
arrested Monday near Orvieto, a medieval hilltop town about 70
miles north of Rome. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center display)
</P>
<P>
   MARTHA-STEWART (Undated) _ For her millions of devotees, it is
no doubt hard to imagine a world without Martha Stewart _ a world
without her next foolproof recipe, her next decorating idea, her
latest palette of paint colors, some fresh uses for glue guns. But
can Ms. Stewart, known for her micro-attentive style, ever relax
her grip enough to let potential successors share her spotlight?
And if she does, can she maintain her aura among her fans? By Diana
B. Henriques.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo and graphic are being sent to NYT photo/graphics
clients. Non-subscribers can make individual purchase by calling
(888) 603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.)
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET.)
