<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, OCTOBER 12
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CONGRESS-CRUISE-SHIPS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Oct. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Oct. 7.,
about a Coast Guard inquiry into a fire on Sept. 19 aboard the
Carnival Cruise Lines ship Tropicale misstated the length of time
the ship was disabled. The ship was adrift in the Gulf of Mexico
for 21 hours, not two days, before the crew was able to restart one
engine.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-COMPUTER-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Oct. 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Oct. 6,
about new iMac models misidentified the video editing software that
will be packaged with the iMac DV. The program is iMovie, not Final
Cut Pro.
</P>
